{
  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The proposal fails to demonstrate that the property is suitable for conversion; the applicant has failed to demonstrate that the original dwellinghouse is greater than 130 square metres in area, and therefore fails the minimum size threshold to be eligible for conversion. The proposal is therefore unacceptable in principle, contrary to Local Plan policy SC6 (Managing building conversions and sub-division of the existing housing stock).",
    "Reason : 2 - The proposal fails to promote sustainable travel and has not demonstrated that the parking arrangements would not lead to conditions prejudicial to pedestrian safety contrary to Local Plan policy EC2 and London Plan policy T6.1.",
    "Reason : 3 - The proposal would fail to provide adequate waste and recycling facilities, contrary to Local Plan policies SC6 (Managing building conversions and sub-division of the existing housing stock) and EQ7 (Sustainable waste management) and the Recycling and Refuse Guidance."
